    <h2>Iron Maiden Multiballs</h2>
    <h5><b>Mummy Multiball</b></h5>
    <p>
        <h6>Qualifying:</h6>
        <li>Shoot captive ball twice (5 times for subsequent multiballs) to light the Mummy Lock (center ramp).</li>
        <li>After locking the ball, spell MUMMY at the captive ball with 5 more shots to qualify Mummy Multiball.</li>
        <li>Shoot captive ball one more time to start Mummy Multiball.</li>
        <!-- <li><i>Note - 3rd and subsequent Mummy Multiballs require two hits per MUMMY letter.</i></li> -->
    </p>
    <p>
        <h6>Play:</h6>
        <li>Shoot switches to qualify captive ball jackpot. </li>
        <li>Each jackpot spots a MUMMY letter. </li>
        <li>Spell MUMMY to light Super Jackpot at the bullseye target. </li>
        <li><i>Note - shoot yellow shots for an add a ball (you can get up to 3 add a balls).</i></li>
    </p>


    <h5><b>Trooper Multiball</b></h5>
    <p>
        <h6>Qualifying:</h6>
        <li>Complete the drop targets bank (twice the first time) to light the green arrow shots.</li>
        <li>Hit the green arrow orbit shot(s) to virtually lock a ball.</li>
        <li>Lock 3 balls to start Trooper Multiball.</li>
        <!-- <li><i>Note - 3rd and subsequent Mummy Multiballs require two hits per MUMMY letter.</i></li> -->
    </p>
    <p>
        <h6>Play:</h6>
        <li>Shoot blue shots for 1x jackpot ( will unlight when collected). </li>
        <li>Collecting 3 jackpots lights the first Super Jackpot at the corresponding target.</li>
        <li>Scoring the Super Jackpot relights collected jackpots with +1x scoring, while uncollected shots remain lit at their previous scoring level. </li>
        <li>Jackpot shot color progression denoting which shots are multiplied at different levels is reverse rainbow (blue, green, etc). </li>
        <li>Completing the drop targets during Trooper Multiball will light the bullseye target to fire the cannon (indicated by the rainbow flashing arrow). </li>
        <li><i>Note - You can collect multiple cannon shots in a single multiball.</i></li>
    </p>



